cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with network densification and handover management in cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 

2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses stochastic geometry to develop a mathematical model for quantifying the performance of the proposed handover scheme, which involves information theory concepts. 

3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with communication and networking aspects of cellular networks, such as handover management and network densification. 

4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed handover scheme involves coordination and cooperation among multiple base stations, which can be seen as a control system. 

5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses user throughput as a performance metric, which is related to multimedia applications that require high data rates.
